HOUSE BILL 1632
J1 6lr3633
By: Delegate Metzgar
Introduced and read first time: February 25, 2026
Assigned to: Rules and Executive Nominations
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Anthony McCarthy Task Force to Study Dialysis Outcomes
3 FOR the purpose of establishing the Anthony McCarthy Task Force to Study Dialysis
4 Outcomes; and generally relating to the Anthony McCarthy Task Force to Study
5 Dialysis Outcomes.
6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That:
8 (a) There is an Anthony McCarthy Task Force to Study Dialysis Outcomes.
9 (b) The Task Force consists of the following members:
10 (1) two members of the Senate of Maryland, appointed by the President of
11 the Senate;
12 (2) two members of the House of Delegates, appointed by the Speaker of
13 the House;
14 (3) the Secretary of Health, or the Secretary’s designee;
15 (4) one additional representative of the Maryland Department of Health,
16 designated by the Secretary of Health; and
17 (5) the following members, appointed by the Governor:
18 (i) one physician licensed in the State who specializes in urology;
19 (ii) one physician licensed in the State who specializes in nephrology;
20 and
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
