2 HOUSE BILL 1632
1 (iii) two individuals in the State who have received dialysis
2 treatment.
3 (c) The Governor shall designate the chair of the Task Force.
4 (d) The Maryland Department of Health shall provide staff for the Task Force.
5 (e) A member of the Task Force:
6 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Task Force; but
7 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
8 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
9 (f) The Task Force shall:
10 (1) evaluate current dialysis patient outcomes in the State;
11 (2) study methods, programs, and approaches that would improve dialysis
12 patient outcomes, including:
13 (i) increased access to in–home dialysis treatment options;
14 (ii) the establishment of a training program for individuals receiving
15 in–home dialysis treatment and the individuals’ caretakers;
16 (iii) the creation of a mandatory certification for home health aides
17 who provide support to individuals receiving in–home dialysis treatment;
18 (iv) the establishment of a grant program to provide monetary
19 support to dialysis patients, including for home modifications for individuals receiving
20 in–home dialysis treatments;
21 (v) the creation of a food–as–medicine grant program for dialysis
22 patients to have reliable access to affordable, renal–friendly foods;
23 (vi) public service campaigns to educate individuals about kidney
24 health; and
25 (vii) community screening events for kidney–related medical
26 concerns; and
27 (3) make legislative recommendations regarding methods to improve
28 dialysis patient outcomes while minimizing taxpayer burdens.

HOUSE BILL 1632 3
1 (g) On or before May 31, 2027, the Task Force shall report its findings and
2 recommendations to the General Assembly, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State
3 Government Article.
4 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
5 1, 2026. It shall remain effective for a period of 1 year and 1 month and, at the end of June
6 30, 2027, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall be
7 abrogated and of no further force and effect.

